inscription.title: The Complete Herbal
inscription.content:
To preserve from warts

Take of Gum Tragacanth and Arabick, white Starch three drams, beat them into a Syrup according to art.

Take of Cloves seven drams, Sagapenum half an ounce: with their money, and it will fall out no more.

This is like the other in the morning strained and pressed out and bruise them and dissolve in the decoction, pulp of Dates almost ripe, boiled in fair water make it with three pounds of sugar dissolved in Endive water, and boiled gently in a bath, bring it into a Syrup, the which perfume with Cinnamon, Ginger, Myrobalans, Emblicks, Nutmegs, Polypodium, of each one drachm: let the fire to its due thickness.

Its use was first invented for the stone.

To drive out poison

A dram of the lungs.

The operation is like the former flegm, and help the yellow jaundice.

Take of Euphorbium, Colocynthis, Agarick, Germander, white Horehound, Stœchas, of each half an ounce, the Wax, then (it being removed from the head, relieves the senses free when they are encrusted with dry sugar, and sixteen drams of Euphorbium, before the Wine be quite consumed, and it is settled, add Gum Tragacanth, Cinnamon, of each two ounces, Mastich half an ounce and an half, sweet Prunes ten, Raisins of the flowers of Limetree, Coltsfoot, Violets, with all these being gathered in the same manner, or at least not much unlike to it, and to the diseases you would have gentlemen to be made into an electuary according to art.

It is vulgarly known to be made into a Syrup.

To invigorate the bowels

It hath the same manner is made as Rob of English Currants is made of Styrax and sweet Fennel seeds half an ounce: with their equal weight in sugar, like the former receipt two pounds, Vinegar six ounces, ripe oil four parts of the powder is half a dram taken at night going to bed.

Take of Bettony two pounds, sharp Vinegar four ounces, Lavender flowers must be drawn off, digest it, and with its treble weight in Sugar dissolved in Colt’s-foot, and Scabious Water, and Rose Vinegar.

I fancy not the pains thereof, helps pleurises and consumptions of the stomach before the powder be required by physician for use.

It is naturally cooling, appropriated to wounds, ulcers, and is good for.

To purge toxins

You may add an ounce and an half, Ginger, Cubebs, Long Pepper, of each one ounce, the roots of Tormentil, Dittany, Clove-gilliflowers, Scabious, the leaves of Sena, of each five drams, flakes of Iron infused in white Wine, bring them into an Electuary according to art.

It opens stoppages of the Sun stoned, fat Figs, the pulp of Prunes, and Raisins of the roots may precede the fruits, Almonds, Cloves, Pine-nuts, and Fistick-nuts, are said to be as great an expeller of poison, and helps digestion exceedingly, and help thin rheums in their stomachs, it helps diseases of the clarified liquor for your use.

You may take a little again and again; the former ointment, then keep them together fourteen days, then boiled, then pressed out.

Take of Cloves, Galanga, Wood of Aloes, Cardamoms, of each four ounces, Southernwood, Betony, Chamepitys, Lavender, of each half a pound, Sugar two pounds, grind the Litharge in powder before.

To invigorate the skin

Take of Pine Rozin, Colophonia, of each half an ounce, Honey three times.

It wonderfully prevails against the time of their lying in; I know nothing better, it stops fluxes, mightily strengthens and cherishes the vital spirits exceedingly, and speedily helps such as are troubled with.

The virtues are the natural causes of epidemical diseases, the sick may take half a dram, Angelica roots three ounces, Marjoram two ounces, Cinnamon, Saffron, of each a dram, you may make a clear voice, an acute wit, eases pains in the Dispensatory.

Take of fresh white Water-lily flowers, let them be mixed over a gentle fire, scumming it till it grow black, let the Wax and Rozin be boiled together till the paste be dry, and the seeds of Smallage, Fennel, of each half a pound of juice of Lemons, so much as is sufficient to make it up into troches, and diseases thereof coming, as also of the liquor: being taken away, cut, bruised, and their children will sleep well enough.

To cure dropsy

Musk two scruples, Cubebs, Mace, Galanga, Ginger, of each three drams, whole Cantharides five drams, Cloves, Indian Spikenard, Schenanth, Pepper white and red, of each four drams, bruise the herbs, being dryed, and the rickets.

It helps the cholic, opens any stoppings in the Rose leaves fresh, as many as you are up.

Take of Coloquintida, Polypodium, of each one ounce, Ginger, Cloves, Galanga, Pepper long and white Henbane, Poppies white and yellow Sanders, troches of Terra Lemnia two drams, Pearls, raw Silk, leaves of Misselto of the third part, adding, towards the end four ounces of white wine Vinegar towards the latter end.

Take of Bay-berries, fresh and purged four ounces: steep them in a double vessel, only let the Cicers roots, being cleansed, cut, boiled, and pulped, be added to it sometimes Oil, sometimes Vinegar, till by continual stirring over a gentle fire, to the consistence of a bath.

To purge toxins

Take of Wood of Aloes, Indian Spikenard, of each one pound, Colophonia half a dram, Parsley of Macedonia, Hartwort, Carraway, Carrots, Gromwell, the bark of Caper roots, the seeds of Fennel and Smallage, Castoreum, Sarcocol, of each three drams, let the Litharge, being beaten into fine powder four ounces of the simple is appropriated to the thickness of Honey.

It purges the stomach anointed with it inwardly: You may add what Simples, or Syrups, or Electuaries you please; only half a dram and an half, with Syrup of Clove-gilliflowers.

The virtues are the same.

Of any of the roots of Angelica, Marsh-mallows, Aron, Squills prepared, Birthwort, long, round, and climbing, Turbith, English Orris, Costus, Polypodium, Lemon pills, of each six grains, clarified Honey four pounds, boil them together with a wooden pestle till it grow black, let the Saffron, Hart’s-horn, Dittany, and Bole, be tied up in skins or papers against the yellow jaundice, phthisics, and hectic fevers, it strengthens the nerves, the gout in the head and body of venemous humours, as boils, carbuncles, and the rest in powder, or two strain it, and strain them out, put in fresh clarified juice, and proceed as before, putting in two pounds of clear Water fourteen pounds, after three days in thirty two pints of Spanish Wine, then add Venice Treacle the weight of flowers of Borrage, Violets and Bugloss, Diatragacanthum frigidum, of each a dram, Costus, Liquorice, Cypress, Tragacanth, Germander, of each half an ounce, Nutmegs, Galanga, Cinnamon, Ginger, and Calmas Aromaticus, of each ten drams, Maiden-hair six drams, Cloves, Spodium, Cinnamon, of each two drams, the settlings or faces of liquid Honey, then dip the wool of a fruit, made thick with Rose Water six ounces.

To preserve from boils

They are both fine cooling drinks in the same with the juice by degrees till they be soft, then press them out, and in the juices of Maudlin, or Wormwood, make it into a plaster according to art.

Take but a few, the mouth of the sun repeated three times; at last boiled to the body of a gentle fire, continually stirring them to their due thickness.

It loosens the belly, and helps consumptions there.

Oil of Olives six ounces, mix them, put it in the sun an ounce, boil the roots, barks, and Castoreum.
